{"lemma":"مَغْرِبِ","slug":"مَغْرِبِ","root":"غ.ر.ب","root_slug":"غ-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَغْرِب","root":"غرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31622","n31623"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place or time of sunset","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: مَطْلَع (maṭlaʕ)"},{"text":"حَتَّى إِذَا بَلَغَ مَغْرِبَ الشَّمْسِ وَجَدَهَا تَغْرُبُ فِي عَيْنٍ حَمِئَةٍ","english":"until he reached the setting ˹point˺ of the sun, which appeared to him to be setting in a spring of murky water."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sunset prayer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"west","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ فَإِنَّ اللَّهَ يَأْتِي بِالشَّمْسِ مِنَ الْمَشْرِقِ فَأْتِ بِهَا مِنَ الْمَغْرِبِ فَبُهِتَ الَّذِي كَفَرَ","english":"Abraham said: Lo! Allah causeth the sun to rise in the East, so do thou cause it to come up from the West. Thus was the disbeliever abashed."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evening"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to Moroccanize, to make Moroccan"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the root غ ر ب (ḡ r b) of غَرْب (ḡarb, “west, occident”). Compare Hebrew מַעֲרָב (maʿărāḇ) and Aramaic ܡܥܪܒܐ (maʿrəḇā)"},"ipa":["/maɣ.rib/","/muɣ.rub/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31622","headword_ar":"مَغْرِبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magorabN","text_ar":"مَغْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first quarter, in four. places. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu magoriba Al$~amosi","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ مَغْرِبَ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribaAnahaA","text_ar":"مَغْرِبَانَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribaAnaAtihaA","text_ar":"مَغْرِبَانَاتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugayoribaAnahaA","text_ar":"مُغَيْرِبَانَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugayoribaAnaAtihaA","text_ar":"مُغَيْرِبَانَاتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, at sunset."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) [It is said that] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugayoribaAnN","text_ar":"مُغَيْرِبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dim. formed from a word other than that which is its proper source of derivation; being as though formed from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribaAnN","text_ar":"مَغْرِبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L. [Hence it seems that this last word as given above was unknown to, or not admitted by, the authors of these two works.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribN","text_ar":"مَغْرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that conceals, veils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covers, one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magaAribu","text_ar":"مَغَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lucking-places"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wild animals. (Az, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n31623","headword_ar":"مُغْرَبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, latter half. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as an epithet applied to anything: or that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which every partis white;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is the ugliest kind of whiteness. (K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White in the edges of the eyelids;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as an epithet applied to anything: (S:) a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the edges of the eyelids, and the iris of each eye, and the hair of the tail, and every part, are white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) and a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the blaze upon his face extends beyond his eyes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugorabapN","text_ar":"مُغْرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eye which is blue"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gray"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of which the edges of the lids, and the surrounding parts, are white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when the iris also is white, the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_igoraAb","text_ar":"اـِغْرَاب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the utmost degree. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn of day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) so called because of its whiteness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","IAar","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}